
[1]pertilence

   PERT'ILENCE, n. [L. pestilentia, from pestilens; pestis,plague.]

   1. Plague, appropriately so called; but in a general sense, any
   contagious or infectious disease that is epidemic and mortal.

   2. Corruption or moral disease destructive to happiness.

   Profligate habits carry pestilence into the bosom of domestic society.
